    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince we now support dynamic registration for diagnostics, could we use those registrations when making diagnostics pull requests?\n\nI’ve also noticed that not sending an identifier to `textDocument/diagnostic` has a performance impact on larger projects. Additionally, with the server I’m using, not sending an identifier means `interFileDependencies` / `relatedDocumentSupport` won’t work, since those are only enabled for some diagnostic registrations.\n\nI did a quick test here: https://github.com/ZieMcd/neovim/commit/744680647becb0d4267ebc69b6f2cf3f394bd56f, and I’ve already noticed performance improvements. The server is also now sending back `relatedDocuments`.\n\nNot sure if there is any overlap with https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37166\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSending identifiers for registered diagnostics when pulling diagnostcs",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-12T08:58:17Z",
